1
00:00:00,230 --> 00:00:05,600
In this video we are going to compare monolithic and microservice architectures.

2
00:00:05,630 --> 00:00:12,470
By this way, you will could understand which design better fits your business requirements and capacity.

3
00:00:13,710 --> 00:00:17,070
The first comparison is application architecture.

4
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:22,440
Monolithic has a simple, straightforward structure of one undivided unit.

5
00:00:23,010 --> 00:00:29,970
But microservices have a complex structure that consists of various heterogeneous services and databases.

6
00:00:31,590 --> 00:00:34,020
The second comparison is scalability.

7
00:00:34,260 --> 00:00:41,850
Monolithic application is scaled as a whole single unit, but microservices can be scaled independently

8
00:00:41,850 --> 00:00:46,950
and this will save business and development teams a lot of time and resources.

9
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:54,030
This difference between monolithic and microservices encouraged companies to migrate their rapidly growing

10
00:00:54,030 --> 00:01:01,620
applications to microservices in order to derive agility and enable more cost effective approach to

11
00:01:01,620 --> 00:01:02,460
development.

12
00:01:04,190 --> 00:01:07,010
And another comparison is deployment.

13
00:01:07,130 --> 00:01:12,530
Monolithic application provides fast and easy deployment of whole system.

14
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:19,730
On the other hand, microservices can deploy different components in a microservice application independently.

15
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:26,420
This enables frequently and zero downtime deployment and provide CI CD automations.

16
00:01:26,450 --> 00:01:28,430
You can see the picture in here.

17
00:01:28,430 --> 00:01:34,880
You can see the monolithic application has large development teams pushing the code single code base,

18
00:01:34,880 --> 00:01:38,690
and there is one deployment pipeline and deploy the production.

19
00:01:38,990 --> 00:01:45,290
On the other hand, you can see the different teams organized development teams in microservices, and

20
00:01:45,290 --> 00:01:49,820
every team has own code base about the microservice code base.

21
00:01:49,820 --> 00:01:56,450
And every microservice has different development deployment pipelines, and they can deploy independently

22
00:01:56,450 --> 00:01:58,730
and perform CI, CD automations.

23
00:02:00,510 --> 00:02:03,810
Another comparison is development teams.

24
00:02:03,990 --> 00:02:10,410
If your team doesn't have experience with microservices and container systems, building a microservice

25
00:02:10,410 --> 00:02:12,600
based application will be difficult.

26
00:02:12,630 --> 00:02:17,940
Monolithic architecture can be preferable for single developers or small teams.

27
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:24,630
On the other hand, if you have teams skilled in microservice deployments and plan to expand your team

28
00:02:24,630 --> 00:02:29,460
over time, starting with microservices can save your time in the future.

29
00:02:29,730 --> 00:02:36,150
Because microservices provide better flexibility when it comes to team composition and distribution

30
00:02:36,150 --> 00:02:37,890
of tasks and ownership.

